{"title":"Tour de Romandie men’s 2024: Route, start list, how to watch and everything you need to know","link":"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/tour-de-romandie-preview","date":1713540471000,"content":"<p><a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk\">Cyclist</a><br />\n<a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/tour-de-romandie-preview\">Tour de Romandie men’s 2024: Route, start list, how to watch and everything you need to know</a></p>\n\n<p>The Tour de Romandie is a staple for <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/tour-de-france-route-live-tv-guide-startlist-stage-by-stage\" target=\"_blank\">Tour de France</a> preparations, with past winners including Tour champions Chris Froome, Geraint Thomas, Bradley Wiggins and Cadel Evans. The 2024 men’s edition starts on Tuesday 23rd April and runs until Sunday 28th April.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Taking the riders through the French-speaking Romandy region in the west of Switzerland, which includes the cantons of Geneva, Jura, Neuchâtel and Vaud as well as parts of Bern, Fribourg and Valais, there is usually a healthy amount of hard climbing and good time-trial action for the GC specialists to sink their teeth into.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The 2024 parcours will feature a heavy amount of time-trialling with both a prologue <em>and </em>a time-trial on Stage 3. Two summit finishes at Les Marécottes and Leysin will also prove crucial in the battle for overall victory. Favourites for the 2024 race include Spanish wonderkid Juan Ayuso, former Tour de France champion Egan Bernal and Bora-Hansgrohe’s double threat of Jai Hindley and Sasha Vlasov.</p>\n\n\n<div>\r\n                <div>\r\n                   <div>\r\n                      <div>\r\n                         <h4><span>Related Posts</span></h4>\r\n                      </div>\r\n                      <div>\r\n                         <div>\r\n                            <div>\r\n                            <article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/vincenzo-nibali-cyclist\">Shark tale: Vincenzo Nibali profile</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article><article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/giro-ditalia-watch-live-stages-route-riders-teams-start-list\">Giro d’Italia 2024 route headlined by double Monte Grappa ascent</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article><article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/tour-de-france-route-live-tv-guide-startlist-stage-by-stage\">Men’s Tour de France 2024 route announced: What will riders face on the road from Florence to Nice?</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article><article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/liege-bastogne-liege-route-riders-and-all-you-need-to-know\">Liège-Bastogne-Liège 2024: Route, riders, how to watch and all you need to know</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article></div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                        <div>\r\n                                            <span></span><span></span><span></span>\r\n                                        </div>\r\n                                        <div>\r\n                                            <div>\r\n                                                <div></div>\r\n                                            </div>\r\n                                        </div>\r\n                                        <div>\r\n                                            <div>\r\n                                                <div></div>\r\n                                            </div>\r\n                                        </div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                </div>\r\n                                <div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                        <span></span>\r\n                                        <span></span>\r\n                                        <span></span>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                </div>\r\n                                \r\n                            </div>\r\n                        </div>\r\n                        </div>\n\n\n<h2>Tour de Romandie 2024: Key information</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"647\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/2023_1-scaled-romandie23-peloton-970x647.jpg\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/2023_1-scaled-romandie23-peloton-970x646.jpg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/2023_1-scaled-romandie23-peloton-300x200.jpg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/2023_1-scaled-romandie23-peloton-768x512.jpg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/2023_1-scaled-romandie23-peloton-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/2023_1-scaled-romandie23-peloton-2048x1366.jpg 2048w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/2023_1-scaled-romandie23-peloton-750x500.jpg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/2023_1-scaled-romandie23-peloton-1140x760.jpg 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/2023_1-scaled-romandie23-peloton-465x310.jpg 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/2023_1-scaled-romandie23-peloton-620x413.jpg 620w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/2023_1-scaled-romandie23-peloton-350x233.jpg 350w\" /><figcaption>Tour de Romandie</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Dates:</strong> 23rd April-28th April</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Start:</strong> Payerne, Switzerland</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Finish:</strong> Vernier, Switzerland</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Stages:</strong> Five (six with prologue)</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>UK television coverage:</strong> Eurosport, Discovery+</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Most wins:</strong> Stephen Roche (three)</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>2023 winner:</strong> Adam Yates</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<h2>Tour de Romandie 2024 route</h2>\n\n\n<div>\n<figure><img width=\"483\" height=\"669\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/GK4_Cp4W8AAwX1v.jpg\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/GK4_Cp4W8AAwX1v.jpg 483w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/GK4_Cp4W8AAwX1v-217x300.jpg 217w\" /><figcaption>Tour de Romandie</figcaption></figure></div>\n\n\n<h2>Tour de Romandie 2024: stage by stage preview</h2>\n\n\n\n<h3>Prologue: Tuesday 23rd April, Payerne – Payerne, 2.28km</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"342\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/romandie-stage-1-970x342.png\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/romandie-stage-1-970x342.png 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/romandie-stage-1-300x106.png 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/romandie-stage-1-768x271.png 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/romandie-stage-1-750x264.png 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/romandie-stage-1-1140x402.png 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/romandie-stage-1.png 1200w\" /><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>With a prologue just longer than 2 kilometres, the opening day of racing in Switzerland will be short and sweet. So short that most riders will complete the course within the time length of most commercial pop songs. That said, there will be plenty of corners and road furniture that could take the riders out of their rhythm.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Stage 1: Wednesday 24th April, Château d’Oex – Fribourg, 165.7km</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"342\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/romandie-stage-2-970x342.png\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/romandie-stage-2-970x342.png 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/romandie-stage-2-300x106.png 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/romandie-stage-2-768x271.png 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/romandie-stage-2-750x264.png 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/romandie-stage-2-1140x402.png 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/romandie-stage-2.png 1200w\" /><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The first road stage will take the riders out of the chocolate box mountains briefly. Some small bumps along the way will test the peloton, but a routine sprint approach to the line in Fribourg, a town which sits on the eastern frontier of Switzerland’s French-speaking region. </p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Stage 2: Thursday 25th April, Fribourg – Salvan/Les Marécottes, 171.0km</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"342\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/romandie-stage-3-970x342.png\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/romandie-stage-3-970x342.png 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/romandie-stage-3-300x106.png 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/romandie-stage-3-768x271.png 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/romandie-stage-3-750x264.png 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/romandie-stage-3-1140x402.png 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/romandie-stage-3.png 1200w\" /><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The much-anticipated Swiss Alps will make an appearance on Stage 2. With two substantial climbs on the menu here in Les Mosses (12.9km at 4.1%) and the finishing climb of Les Marécottes (10km at 7.3%). The mountain-top challenge will take the riders onto slopes maxing out at 14% in gradient.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Stage 3: Friday 26th April, Oron – Oron,  ITT, 15.5km</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"342\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/romandie-stage-4-970x342.png\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/romandie-stage-4-970x342.png 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/romandie-stage-4-300x106.png 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/romandie-stage-4-768x271.png 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/romandie-stage-4-750x264.png 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/romandie-stage-4-1140x402.png 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/romandie-stage-4.png 1200w\" /><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The profile for the race’s second race of truth is ruthlessly undulating, with an initial 3km climb right from the start. From here it’s up and down all the way to the end. Expect a wild set of results on the time-sheets – anything goes in a Tour de Romandie time-trial, especially if it’s as bite-size as this.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Stage 4: Saturday 27th April, Saillon – Leysin, 151.7km</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"342\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/04/romandie-stage-5-970x342.png\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/04/romandie-stage-5-970x342.png 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/04/romandie-stage-5-300x106.png 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/04/romandie-stage-5-768x271.png 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/04/romandie-stage-5-750x265.png 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/04/romandie-stage-5-1140x402.png 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/04/romandie-stage-5.png 1261w\" /><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The summit-finish sequel offers a much tougher Toblerone-like profile. Two Alpine tests will preface the final climb at Leysin. Over 10km in length and at an average gradient of 5.9%, this stage will offer a last-chance saloon for anyone to make necessary time gaps ahead of the Tour de Romandie’s conclusion the next day.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Stage 5: Sunday 28th April, Vernier – Vernier, 150.8km</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"342\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/romandie-stage-6-970x342.png\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/romandie-stage-6-970x342.png 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/romandie-stage-6-300x106.png 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/romandie-stage-6-768x271.png 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/romandie-stage-6-750x264.png 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/romandie-stage-6-1140x402.png 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/romandie-stage-6.png 1200w\" /><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Don’t let the profile above fool you. This stage is not as challenging as it presents itself to be. The short kicker of Dardagny (2km at 4.4%) provides a small opportunity for gaps to be made, but in reality this should be one for the sprinters or a breakaway effort.</p>\n\n\n<div>\r\n                <div>\r\n                   <div>\r\n                      <div>\r\n                         <h4><span>Related Posts</span></h4>\r\n                      </div>\r\n                      <div>\r\n                         <div>\r\n                            <div>\r\n                            <article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/vincenzo-nibali-cyclist\">Shark tale: Vincenzo Nibali profile</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article><article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/giro-ditalia-watch-live-stages-route-riders-teams-start-list\">Giro d’Italia 2024 route headlined by double Monte Grappa ascent</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article><article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/tour-de-france-route-live-tv-guide-startlist-stage-by-stage\">Men’s Tour de France 2024 route announced: What will riders face on the road from Florence to Nice?</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article><article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/liege-bastogne-liege-route-riders-and-all-you-need-to-know\">Liège-Bastogne-Liège 2024: Route, riders, how to watch and all you need to know</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article></div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                        <div>\r\n                                            <span></span><span></span><span></span>\r\n                                        </div>\r\n                                        <div>\r\n                                            <div>\r\n                                                <div></div>\r\n                                            </div>\r\n                                        </div>\r\n                                        <div>\r\n                                            <div>\r\n                                                <div></div>\r\n                                            </div>\r\n                                        </div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                </div>\r\n                                <div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                        <span></span>\r\n                                        <span></span>\r\n                                        <span></span>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                </div>\r\n                                \r\n                            </div>\r\n                        </div>\r\n                        </div>\n\n\n<h2>Tour de Romandie 2024: live TV and streaming guide</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"647\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/2023-romandie_ayuso-970x647.jpg\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/2023-romandie_ayuso-970x646.jpg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/2023-romandie_ayuso-300x200.jpg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/2023-romandie_ayuso-768x512.jpg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/2023-romandie_ayuso-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/2023-romandie_ayuso-2048x1365.jpg 2048w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/2023-romandie_ayuso-750x500.jpg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/2023-romandie_ayuso-1140x760.jpg 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/2023-romandie_ayuso-465x310.jpg 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/2023-romandie_ayuso-620x413.jpg 620w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/2023-romandie_ayuso-350x233.jpg 350w\" /><figcaption>Keystone SDA / Tour de Romandie</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The Tour de Romandie will be shown throughout the week on Eurosport and <a href=\"https://www.discoveryplus.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Discovery+</a> in the UK, <a href=\"https://www.max.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Max</a> and <a href=\"https://www.flobikes.com/\" target=\"_blank\">FloBikes</a> in the United States, Canada can catch it on FloBikes too.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>If it’s not being shown in your country, you may be able to watch coverage using a VPN – Virtual Private Network – which allows users to mask their IP address and watch geo-blocked content, provided they don’t need to pay for a subscription. This is also helpful for watching paid-for coverage while travelling abroad in countries without access. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>One such example is <a href=\"https://go.expressvpn.com/m5yJGZ\" target=\"_blank\">ExpressVPN</a>, which is very <a href=\"https://www.independent.co.uk/advisor/vpn/expressvpn-review\" target=\"_blank\">well reviewed</a>, has specific advice for watching cycling and costs £5.36 per month with three months free. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Other options include <a href=\"https://go.skimresources.com/?id=205647X1684865&amp;xs=1&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fnordvpn.com%2F\" target=\"_blank\">NordVPN</a>, <a href=\"https://go.skimresources.com/?id=205647X1684865&amp;xs=1&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fsurfshark.com%2F\" target=\"_blank\">Surfshark</a> and <a href=\"https://go.skimresources.com/?id=205647X1684865&amp;xs=1&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.kaspersky.co.uk%2F\" target=\"_blank\">Kapersky</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Read more: <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/how-to-watch-cycling\" target=\"_blank\">How to watch cycling post-GCN</a></strong> </li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<p>TV and streaming schedule below is listed in BST time and subject to change by broadcasters.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Prologue: Tuesday 23rd April</h3>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Eurosport 2: </strong>14:30-16:45<br /><strong>Discovery+: </strong>14:30-16:50</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Stage 1: Wednesday 24th April</h3>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Eurosport 1: </strong>14:30-16:45<br /><strong><strong>Discovery+</strong>:</strong> 14:30-16:50</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Stage 2: Thursday 25th April</h3>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Eurosport 2: </strong>14:30-16:45<br /><strong><strong>Discovery+</strong>:</strong> 14:30-16:50</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Stage 3: Friday 26th April</h3>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Eurosport 2: </strong>14:30-16:45<br /><strong><strong>Discovery+</strong>:</strong> 14:30-16:50</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Stage 4: Saturday 27th April</h3>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Eurosport 2: </strong>13:00-15:15<br /><strong><strong>Discovery+</strong>: </strong>13:00-15:20</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Stage 5: Sunday 28th April</h3>\n\n\n\n<p><strong><strong>Discovery+</strong>: </strong>13:00-15:20</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Tour de Romandie 2024: Start list</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"647\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/2023_3-scaled-romandie23-hayter-970x647.jpg\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/2023_3-scaled-romandie23-hayter-970x646.jpg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/2023_3-scaled-romandie23-hayter-300x200.jpg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/2023_3-scaled-romandie23-hayter-768x512.jpg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/2023_3-scaled-romandie23-hayter-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/2023_3-scaled-romandie23-hayter-2048x1366.jpg 2048w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/2023_3-scaled-romandie23-hayter-750x500.jpg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/2023_3-scaled-romandie23-hayter-1140x760.jpg 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/2023_3-scaled-romandie23-hayter-465x310.jpg 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/2023_3-scaled-romandie23-hayter-620x413.jpg 620w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/2023_3-scaled-romandie23-hayter-350x233.jpg 350w\" /><figcaption>Tour de Romandie</figcaption><figcaption>Tour de Romandie</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<div><p><em>Data powered by <a href=\"https://firstcycling.com/race.php?r=12&amp;y=2